    assignment_name VARCHAR(255),
    course_id INT REFERENCES courses(course_id),
    due_date DATE
);

    course_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    course_name VARCHAR(255),
    instructor_name VARCHAR(255),
    credits INT
);

    assignment_name VARCHAR(255),
    course_id INT REFERENCES courses(course_id),
    due_date DATE
);

    submission_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT REFERENCES students(student_id),
    assignment_id INT REFERENCES assignments(assignment_id),
    submission_date DATE,
    grade FLOAT

    submission_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT REFERENCES students(student_id),
    assignment_id INT REFERENCES assignments(assignment_id),
    submission_date DATE,
    grade FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE courses (
    course_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    course_name VARCHAR(255),
    instructor_name VARCHAR(255),
    credits INT
);</t><stat>select student_name, avg(grade) as average_grade from students join submissions on students.student_id = submissions.student_id group by student_name having average_grade >= 80;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE students (
    student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_name VARCHAR(255),
    email VARCHAR(255),
    course_id INT REFERENCES courses(course_id)
);

CREATE TABLE submissions (
    submission_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT REFERENCES students(student_id),
    assignment_id INT REFERENCES assignments(assignment_id),
    submission_date DATE,
    grade FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE courses (
    course_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    course_name VARCHAR(255),
    instructor_name VARCHAR(255),
    credits INT
);

CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    assignment_name VARCHAR(255),
    course_id INT REFERENCES courses(course_id),
    due_date DATE
);</t><stat>SELECT student_name, AVG(grade) AS average_grade FROM students JOIN submissions ON students.student_id = submissions.student_id GROUP BY student_name HAVING average_grade >= 80;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE students (
    student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_name VARCHAR(255),
    email VARCHAR(255),

);

    student_name VARCHAR(255),
    email VARCHAR(255),
    course_id INT REFERENCES courses(course_id)
);

CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    assignment_name VARCHAR(255),
    course_id INT REFERENCES courses(course_id),
    due_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE submissions (
    submission_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT REFERENCES students(student_id),
    assignment_id INT REFERENCES assignments(assignment_id),
    submission_date DATE,
    grade FLOAT
);</t><stat>SELECT course_name, COUNT(DISTINCT instructor_name) AS total_instructors FROM courses GROUP BY course_name;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE courses (
    course_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    course_name VARCHAR(255),
    instructor_name VARCHAR(255),
    credits INT
);
